<paragraph blockId="11.[880,1387,737,758]" box="[880,1387,737,758]" pageId="11" pageNumber="708">
<heading box="[880,1387,737,758]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="11" pageNumber="708" reason="2">
<taxonomicName authority="WILLISTON, 1887" authorityName="Williston" authorityYear="1887" box="[880,1387,737,758]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="708" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbipenne">
<emphasis box="[880,1178,737,758]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="708">COPESTYLUM LIMBIPENNE</emphasis>
WILLISTON, 1887
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[826,1441,775,981]" pageId="11" pageNumber="708">
<emphasis box="[826,1086,775,797]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="708">Larva and puparium:</emphasis>
Anterior fold with a narrow spicule band. Crochets of metathoracic prolegs forming a U-shaped band. Metathorax with lateral folds bearing broad setae at sensilla 4 and 5. Anal lobe with spicules. Posterior breathing tube with AP 1.5¥ length of TR, smooth, shining and tapering. Pupal spiracles about 0.94¥ length of AP.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="709" pageId="11" pageNumber="708" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[826,1441,1022,1289]" pageId="11" pageNumber="708">
<emphasis box="[826,1328,1022,1044]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="708">
Taxonomic notes: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Williston" authorityYear="1887" box="[1051,1328,1022,1043]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="708" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbipenne">Copestylum limbipenne</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is most similar to other members of the Marginatum group in having the AP longer than the width of the TR. It is distinguished from all these species except 
<taxonomicName authority="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier, 2009" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="708" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncatum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="708">C. truncatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[883,972,1145,1166]" pageId="11" pageNumber="708" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the narrow band of spicules on the anterior fold and U-shaped arrangement of crochets on the mesothoracic prolegs. It is separated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="708" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="708">C. truncatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the tapering AP, which is longer than the width of the TR.
</paragraph>
